a spokesman for Mr Corbyn said he would `` stand in respectful silence '' and that he would acknowledge `` the heroism of the Royal Air Force in the Battle of Britain . ''
however , a member of Mr Corbyn 's shadow cabinet , Owen Smith , told BBC Two 's Newsnight that a Labour leader would recommend the national anthem to sing `` regardless '' of his belief that the monarchy should be abolished .
nearly a dozen shadow ministers refused to serve in Mr Corby 's top team , quoting differences in the economy , defence and foreign affairs , and only less than a sixth of the parliamentary party initially supported him as leader .
the BBC 's political correspondent , Robin Brant , says political differences in the work are also `` staged '' following the appointment of Mr Corby over his position in the European Union and the government 's benefit cap .
