the leader of the Workers ' Party , which promised a different approach to policy , says he has ideas `` from the crowd '' to questions for Mr Cameron and has received more than 30,000 proposals .
MP Islington North says the PMQ is too confrontational and that it will refrain from both the `` post-finished response , '' and the Ozzy trade , and instead promises to focus on important issues such as poverty , inequality and the challenges faced by young people .
